SIMPLE: niggle
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Niggle
<hw>Nig"gle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Niggled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Niggling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Dim. of Prov. E.
<ets>nig</ets> to clip money; cf. also Prov. E. <ets>nig</ets> a small
piece.]</ety> <def>To trifle with; to deceive; to mock.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Niggle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Niggle
<hw>Nig"gle</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To trifle or
play.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Take heed, daughter,⟦br⟧
You <qex>niggle</qex> not with your conscience and religion.</q>
<rj><qau>Massinger.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To act or walk mincingly.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To fret and snarl about trifles.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Chiefly Eng.)</fld> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To move about
restlessly or without result; to fidget.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>To be finicky or excessively critical; to potter;
esp., to work with excessive care for trifling details, as in
painting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Niggle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Niggle
<hw>Nig"gle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To use,
spend, or do in a petty or trifling manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To elaborate excessively, as in art.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Niggler</ent>⟦br⟧
